1
00:00:00,610 --> 00:00:01,700
[Disclaimer:
All depicted events are fictional

2
00:00:01,730 --> 00:00:02,730
and for entertainment purposes only;
viewer discretion is advised]

3
00:00:14,560 --> 00:00:18,560
[Love Upon a Time Series]

4
00:00:18,760 --> 00:00:19,720
Are you okay?

5
00:00:20,170 --> 00:00:21,030
I'm not.

6
00:00:21,440 --> 00:00:22,380
Nakun.

7
00:00:23,900 --> 00:00:25,180
Don't force him.

8
00:00:25,770 --> 00:00:27,540
- But...
- But what?

9
00:00:28,140 --> 00:00:29,280
[Thee: Are you arriving soon? How about another time?]

10
00:00:29,300 --> 00:00:30,480
[I'm here]

11
00:00:34,800 --> 00:00:36,350
Should I be sent there,

12
00:00:36,480 --> 00:00:38,260
then I shall drag you down with me!!

13
00:01:03,790 --> 00:01:04,790
Klao.

14
00:01:20,980 --> 00:01:22,300
If death is to claim you,

15
00:01:23,740 --> 00:01:25,730
it shall be by my hand,
and mine alone, Phop!

16
00:01:39,009 --> 00:01:40,120
Let go!

17
00:01:41,070 --> 00:01:41,840
Phop!

18
00:01:54,170 --> 00:01:54,900
Klao!

19
00:01:55,100 --> 00:01:55,810
My Lord.

20
00:01:56,440 --> 00:01:57,820
- Klao.
- My Lord.

21
00:01:58,190 --> 00:01:59,580
We must get you to the physician at once.

22
00:02:00,100 --> 00:02:00,850
No!

23
00:02:00,880 --> 00:02:01,990
- My Lord.
- No!

24
00:02:02,740 --> 00:02:04,070
I must get to Klao!

25
00:02:04,110 --> 00:02:05,390
Let go of me!

26
00:02:13,510 --> 00:02:16,090
Klao.

27
00:02:20,290 --> 00:02:22,190
Klao!!

28
00:02:37,640 --> 00:02:38,960
The wounds have healed.

29
00:02:39,880 --> 00:02:41,440
But what concerns me is that

30
00:02:41,910 --> 00:02:43,880
he has grown terribly frail,

31
00:02:45,070 --> 00:02:46,520
and I fear a sickness may take hold.

32
00:02:51,730 --> 00:02:53,620
Do take some nourishment, Phop.

33
00:02:54,790 --> 00:02:57,180
I even spent the day
preparing these treats for you.

34
00:03:01,430 --> 00:03:02,590
Phop.

35
00:03:05,060 --> 00:03:06,140
My dear.

36
00:03:11,120 --> 00:03:11,840
Phop!

37
00:03:12,550 --> 00:03:13,230
Phop.

38
00:03:13,880 --> 00:03:14,830
Dear.

39
00:03:16,040 --> 00:03:17,500
- Phop.
- Phop.

40
00:03:17,740 --> 00:03:21,120
Rest now, and take the remedies
as the physician prescribed, I beg.

41
00:03:26,710 --> 00:03:27,710
I cannot, Mother.

42
00:03:30,340 --> 00:03:31,760
I must find Klao.

43
00:03:35,820 --> 00:03:36,520
Phop.

44
00:03:39,570 --> 00:03:40,710
Rest easy now.

45
00:03:42,120 --> 00:03:44,820
I have dispatched the patrols
to search every corner for him.

46
00:03:44,880 --> 00:03:46,960
But a week has already passed, Father.

47
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:51,000
Why, then, has no one yet found him?

48
00:04:00,150 --> 00:04:03,020
Illness may already have taken hold of him.

49
00:04:04,130 --> 00:04:06,130
No one knows what fate has befallen him,

50
00:04:11,430 --> 00:04:13,060
how frightened he may be,

51
00:04:16,410 --> 00:04:18,120
or how troubled his heart is.

52
00:04:22,680 --> 00:04:23,780
Son.

53
00:04:30,840 --> 00:04:31,440
Phop.

54
00:04:32,630 --> 00:04:33,630
Phop.

55
00:04:35,840 --> 00:04:37,010
- Phop...
- Phop.

56
00:04:58,830 --> 00:05:00,740
Sickness may claim you, Phop.

57
00:05:09,660 --> 00:05:10,530
Chuay.

58
00:05:11,440 --> 00:05:12,660
Let us return to our quarters.

59
00:05:13,590 --> 00:05:15,910
Enduring the night like this
will not bring Master Klao back.

60
00:05:16,850 --> 00:05:17,480
No.

61
00:05:20,950 --> 00:05:22,530
If he is to return

62
00:05:24,940 --> 00:05:26,260
and I am not here for him,

63
00:05:28,060 --> 00:05:29,620
who then will tend to his needs?

64
00:05:49,950 --> 00:05:51,760
He has taken no nourishment,

65
00:05:52,600 --> 00:05:54,710
not even water.

66
00:05:56,680 --> 00:05:57,740
He is still lost in his delusions,

67
00:05:58,840 --> 00:06:01,000
writing letters to Master Klao
as he always does.

68
00:06:02,830 --> 00:06:04,360
Endure a little longer, all of us.

69
00:06:05,570 --> 00:06:08,320
Tend well to our lord's heart
and to our own.

70
00:06:10,030 --> 00:06:12,600
The skies that follow a storm
are ever magnificent.

71
00:06:36,870 --> 00:06:38,180
"My dearest,

72
00:06:39,030 --> 00:06:41,920
the father and son have at last confessed.

73
00:06:42,450 --> 00:06:45,970
The evidence was the opium shipment list
concealed beneath their manor,

74
00:06:46,040 --> 00:06:48,050
together with your father's letter,

75
00:06:48,090 --> 00:06:50,820
wherein he declined and threatened
High Lord Horathibodi,

76
00:06:50,880 --> 00:06:53,640
declaring he would denounce
the High Lord to the royal court.

77
00:06:54,820 --> 00:06:56,720
I have been granted the rank of Viscount

78
00:06:57,280 --> 00:06:59,840
for capturing those who defrauded the land.

79
00:07:01,480 --> 00:07:03,620
Yet this triumph...

80
00:07:04,420 --> 00:07:06,160
means nothing,

81
00:07:06,820 --> 00:07:09,630
for it is empty without you by my side
to share in its joy.

82
00:07:16,720 --> 00:07:18,140
Where are you, I wonder?

83
00:07:19,020 --> 00:07:20,600
Do you still remember me, I wonder?

84
00:07:21,840 --> 00:07:25,030
Do you long for me as I long for you
with every breath I draw, I wonder?

85
00:07:26,160 --> 00:07:27,740
Return to me and be my smile

86
00:07:28,120 --> 00:07:30,330
and my happiness once more, Klao.

87
00:07:32,600 --> 00:07:33,520
"Viscount Phop."

88
00:07:45,720 --> 00:07:51,040
[Viscount Phop]

89
00:07:54,680 --> 00:07:59,560
[Yours, Phop]

90
00:09:10,280 --> 00:09:12,640
[Thee: He's left]

91
00:09:16,110 --> 00:09:17,560
I have not yet given up.

92
00:09:18,590 --> 00:09:21,130
I shall find my way to my dearest Klao,

93
00:09:22,140 --> 00:09:23,600
as I have promised.

94
00:09:24,630 --> 00:09:26,130
[Love Upon a Time Series]

95
00:10:36,080 --> 00:10:40,080
[Love Upon a Time Series]

96
00:10:43,390 --> 00:10:44,120
Thank you.

97
00:10:47,410 --> 00:10:48,400
No wonder

98
00:10:48,650 --> 00:10:50,320
you kept asking Nakun to stay.

99
00:10:51,240 --> 00:10:53,360
It was so that
he could speak to the hotel owner himself.

100
00:10:54,550 --> 00:10:55,920
Technically, he's not the owner.

101
00:10:56,470 --> 00:10:58,000
He's here to help his uncle out.

102
00:10:59,850 --> 00:11:01,530
So this friend of yours doesn't have a job,

103
00:11:02,170 --> 00:11:04,640
and he's so behind on rent
that he's about to get evicted.

104
00:11:06,040 --> 00:11:06,840
How about asking him

105
00:11:07,840 --> 00:11:09,330
to work at the cafe on the lower floor

106
00:11:09,370 --> 00:11:10,960
while he searches for another job?

107
00:11:12,100 --> 00:11:13,400
Whoa.

108
00:11:13,440 --> 00:11:15,440
You're such a generous soul.

109
00:11:16,680 --> 00:11:19,320
Still, you're not as handsome as I am.

110
00:11:19,440 --> 00:11:20,280
Thee, come here.

111
00:11:25,220 --> 00:11:26,800
He's helping us out, alright?

112
00:11:29,050 --> 00:11:30,220
Thank you kindly.

113
00:11:49,620 --> 00:11:50,920
Are you okay with this, Nakun?

114
00:11:51,470 --> 00:11:52,680
- Whoa.
- Gorgeous, isn't it?

115
00:11:53,120 --> 00:11:54,880
- What do you think?
- This place is massive.

116
00:11:56,870 --> 00:11:57,600
Let me help you.

117
00:12:20,240 --> 00:12:21,930
People say life gets turned upside down

118
00:12:22,320 --> 00:12:24,220
when you turn 25, right?

119
00:12:26,270 --> 00:12:27,430
I'm in my early 20s,

120
00:12:27,870 --> 00:12:29,450
yet in just a few weeks,

121
00:12:29,770 --> 00:12:31,680
my life has changed a lot.

122
00:12:35,480 --> 00:12:36,640
Come on, let's head inside.

123
00:12:36,740 --> 00:12:37,280
Mm.

124
00:12:39,020 --> 00:12:42,060
And in this new life
I'm trying to get used to,

125
00:12:43,250 --> 00:12:46,040
I've met familiar faces from my past life.

126
00:12:53,350 --> 00:12:55,530
It's not about seeking attention from men.

127
00:12:55,570 --> 00:12:58,770
As women,
we take care of ourselves for ourselves.

128
00:12:58,840 --> 00:13:00,510
Varna, my fragrance brand,

129
00:13:00,540 --> 00:13:02,290
is made for women

130
00:13:02,310 --> 00:13:05,560
who live for themselves
and conquer each day with confidence.

131
00:13:05,600 --> 00:13:07,240
If you're interested,

132
00:13:07,260 --> 00:13:09,000
type 1 in the chat.
[Interested]

133
00:13:10,080 --> 00:13:12,250
Orders have been received. And...

134
00:13:12,270 --> 00:13:13,110
Yes, boss.

135
00:13:14,030 --> 00:13:15,160
Oh, here you go.

136
00:13:15,860 --> 00:13:18,080
Da Hong Pao Frappuccino

137
00:13:18,120 --> 00:13:18,800
with tapioca pearls.

138
00:13:19,200 --> 00:13:20,140
And...

139
00:13:28,710 --> 00:13:31,010
Matcha drink with no added sugar.

140
00:13:33,090 --> 00:13:34,320
Excellent work.

141
00:13:43,640 --> 00:13:44,480
You're taking so long.

142
00:13:54,070 --> 00:13:54,950
I'm thirsty.

143
00:13:55,250 --> 00:13:56,030
Here they are.

144
00:13:56,150 --> 00:13:58,040
Here are your drinks.

145
00:13:59,840 --> 00:14:00,660
Whoa.

146
00:14:01,940 --> 00:14:03,080
They look delicious.

147
00:14:03,980 --> 00:14:05,210
Yours looks really good.

148
00:14:07,890 --> 00:14:09,150
This one's your favorite, right?

149
00:14:11,630 --> 00:14:13,970
You're just rambling.
I'm going to talk to Nakun instead.

150
00:14:14,210 --> 00:14:15,240
How disappointing!

151
00:14:16,040 --> 00:14:17,240
Right now?

152
00:14:18,420 --> 00:14:19,100
Five minutes.

153
00:14:24,640 --> 00:14:25,360
Oh, come on.

154
00:14:25,610 --> 00:14:27,310
Watch where you're going.
I'm in a hurry.

155
00:14:28,960 --> 00:14:29,940
Calm down, Thee.

156
00:14:31,720 --> 00:14:32,760
Mind your words, please.

157
00:14:33,330 --> 00:14:35,120
You were the one who bumped into him.

158
00:14:42,110 --> 00:14:43,420
I'm really sorry.

159
00:14:43,760 --> 00:14:44,780
I didn't mean it.

160
00:14:45,060 --> 00:14:46,310
I'm in a real hurry.

161
00:14:47,440 --> 00:14:48,930
Are you hurt?

162
00:14:51,350 --> 00:14:52,320
Did you get hurt?

163
00:14:53,240 --> 00:14:54,340
No, not a big deal.

164
00:14:55,280 --> 00:14:55,930
Uh...

165
00:14:57,190 --> 00:14:57,970
Oh, it's okay.

166
00:14:58,030 --> 00:14:59,150
Let me clean it up for you.

167
00:15:01,830 --> 00:15:02,640
Okay...

168
00:15:05,530 --> 00:15:07,920
Everyone gets a chance
to start anew in this life.

169
00:15:08,420 --> 00:15:09,640
Whether we cross paths again

170
00:15:09,710 --> 00:15:11,040
is another question.

171
00:15:11,190 --> 00:15:12,320
And if we do,

172
00:15:12,750 --> 00:15:13,840
what would be the next step?

173
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:17,140
A-Chai, it's okay.
I'll mop the floor myself.

174
00:15:17,510 --> 00:15:18,580
Go and prepare him another drink.

175
00:15:18,610 --> 00:15:19,610
No, no.

176
00:15:20,230 --> 00:15:21,200
It's okay.

177
00:15:21,790 --> 00:15:23,000
I'm in a hurry.

178
00:15:23,570 --> 00:15:24,320
So sorry, guys.

179
00:15:25,530 --> 00:15:26,230
"A-Chai"?

180
00:15:27,200 --> 00:15:28,060
He called you "A-Chai"?

181
00:15:28,500 --> 00:15:29,640
No, boss.

182
00:15:29,800 --> 00:15:30,680
My name is Achi.

183
00:15:31,100 --> 00:15:32,360
- Of course, it is.
- Who did he call, then?

184
00:15:32,460 --> 00:15:33,560
I get it.

185
00:15:35,910 --> 00:15:38,120
Who? Who is A-Chai?

186
00:15:39,330 --> 00:15:39,880
Uh...

187
00:15:39,950 --> 00:15:41,400
I didn't say "A-Chai," boss.

188
00:15:41,460 --> 00:15:42,460
I said, "Ch-yes! Ch-yes!"

189
00:15:42,520 --> 00:15:44,040
- "Yes."
- You did say "A-Chai."

190
00:15:44,170 --> 00:15:45,570
No, I said, "yes."

191
00:15:45,600 --> 00:15:47,220
- It really hits the spot.
- You really did say "A-Chai."

192
00:15:47,260 --> 00:15:47,960
It's "yes."

193
00:15:47,990 --> 00:15:49,760
What's wrong with me?!
I can't stop working!

194
00:15:50,480 --> 00:15:51,740
- Like this. Like this.
- Whose name was that?

195
00:15:51,760 --> 00:15:52,560
It's Achi.

196
00:15:52,690 --> 00:15:53,600
Don't be afraid, Achi.

197
00:15:53,640 --> 00:15:55,430
Don't be, sweetie.

198
00:15:55,470 --> 00:15:57,640
- Yes.
- Your name is not A-Chai, it's Achi.

199
00:15:58,230 --> 00:15:59,040
Understood?

200
00:15:59,070 --> 00:15:59,780
Yes, I do.

201
00:16:00,930 --> 00:16:01,930
You've got this.

202
00:16:03,040 --> 00:16:04,120
It's Achi.

203
00:16:12,680 --> 00:16:13,900
[Farmer Phop]

204
00:16:13,920 --> 00:16:15,120
[K-drama Phop]

205
00:16:16,250 --> 00:16:18,680
What kind of new life is Phop having,
I wonder?

206
00:16:28,200 --> 00:16:29,040
Phop.

207
00:16:30,140 --> 00:16:31,840
I still haven't given up on you.

208
00:16:35,140 --> 00:16:37,080
But I think I'll stop being sad now

209
00:16:38,090 --> 00:16:39,650
so that, if I happen to run into you,

210
00:16:40,690 --> 00:16:42,560
all you'll see is my smile.

211
00:16:44,430 --> 00:16:45,220
How does that sound?

212
00:16:50,080 --> 00:16:53,040
In Buddhism, a bond from a past life

213
00:16:53,210 --> 00:16:56,150
is not simply about a couple promising

214
00:16:56,290 --> 00:16:59,700
to love each other across lifetimes,
as it is often portrayed in dramas.

215
00:17:00,420 --> 00:17:02,600
It means that every relationship

216
00:17:02,840 --> 00:17:05,230
and action from the past

217
00:17:06,079 --> 00:17:07,920
helps shape the present.

218
00:17:09,400 --> 00:17:11,440
We meet in this life
because of our shared karma.

219
00:17:12,099 --> 00:17:14,200
That is why our paths cross in this lifetime.

220
00:17:19,950 --> 00:17:20,950
Uh...

221
00:17:21,490 --> 00:17:22,599
Earlier this evening,

222
00:17:23,310 --> 00:17:24,640
you were really cool, Thee.

223
00:17:26,839 --> 00:17:29,160
I thought you were about to
get into a fight with him.

224
00:17:29,660 --> 00:17:31,850
But you kept your cool.

225
00:17:33,940 --> 00:17:35,200
If there had been a fight,

226
00:17:35,320 --> 00:17:36,640
you might have gotten hurt even more.

227
00:17:39,040 --> 00:17:40,160
I care about you, you know.

228
00:17:42,930 --> 00:17:43,830
Let's leave it at that,

229
00:17:44,580 --> 00:17:46,080
or you'll think I'm flirting around again.

230
00:17:46,760 --> 00:17:48,280
Let's get back to the podcast, shall we?

231
00:17:50,820 --> 00:17:52,790
You once asked me
about the concept of multiple lifetimes.

232
00:17:52,860 --> 00:17:55,080
By the way, Pun,
we studied time travel literature today.

233
00:17:55,610 --> 00:17:57,000
The topic was about multiple lifetimes.

234
00:17:58,020 --> 00:17:59,600
Do you believe in stuff like that?

235
00:18:00,190 --> 00:18:03,310
Perhaps our paths crossed in past lives.

236
00:18:04,600 --> 00:18:05,460
Then I don't believe in it.

237
00:18:06,180 --> 00:18:08,040
This lifetime is more than enough.

238
00:18:09,110 --> 00:18:10,420
Can I ask you the same question?

239
00:18:16,040 --> 00:18:18,360
You might not believe this,

240
00:18:20,840 --> 00:18:21,960
but I once dreamed

241
00:18:24,560 --> 00:18:25,880
I was a doctor.

242
00:18:27,490 --> 00:18:29,280
Nakun asked me to buy some plasters,

243
00:18:29,630 --> 00:18:31,130
but I ended up
buying a bag of plaster mix instead.

244
00:18:31,780 --> 00:18:33,800
There's no way I'd ever become a doctor.

245
00:18:41,480 --> 00:18:42,280
Thee.

246
00:18:43,910 --> 00:18:44,850
I also had a dream.

247
00:18:48,760 --> 00:18:50,740
Can you stay
and chat with me at my place?

248
00:18:59,540 --> 00:19:01,420
Since my birthday,

249
00:19:02,290 --> 00:19:04,160
these are the only things
I've been dreaming about.

250
00:19:13,440 --> 00:19:14,520
You're telling me

251
00:19:15,810 --> 00:19:17,010
you can remember your past life?

252
00:19:20,340 --> 00:19:21,640
I don't think so.

253
00:19:22,770 --> 00:19:26,350
Maybe it's because I've been into
those hit period dramas lately.

254
00:19:27,450 --> 00:19:28,680
But...

255
00:19:30,500 --> 00:19:33,720
I've been having the same dreams every night.

256
00:19:37,100 --> 00:19:38,440
In my dreams,

257
00:19:40,910 --> 00:19:43,060
it feels like I once fell for you, Thee.

258
00:19:43,590 --> 00:19:45,080
And I really cared about you.

259
00:19:45,810 --> 00:19:46,960
But you...

260
00:19:47,480 --> 00:19:49,120
kept rejecting me.

261
00:19:50,950 --> 00:19:52,040
When I woke up,

262
00:19:52,570 --> 00:19:54,120
all I could do was cry.

263
00:19:57,270 --> 00:19:58,880
Don't say I'm out of my mind,

264
00:19:59,500 --> 00:20:00,080
but

265
00:20:00,460 --> 00:20:02,040
these dreams felt so real.

266
00:20:12,790 --> 00:20:14,520
They made me realize

267
00:20:17,460 --> 00:20:19,560
I've been really mean to you.

268
00:20:22,280 --> 00:20:24,160
I ditched you countless times.

269
00:20:30,720 --> 00:20:31,760
No, Pun.

270
00:20:31,920 --> 00:20:32,700
Don't cry.

271
00:20:34,180 --> 00:20:35,840
I never get mad at you, you know?

272
00:20:38,560 --> 00:20:40,530
I know that I joke around a lot,

273
00:20:41,680 --> 00:20:43,040
so it's not surprising that you'd ditch me.

274
00:20:45,040 --> 00:20:45,800
But...

275
00:20:46,890 --> 00:20:48,660
